properties.Name: InsuranceEndorsement
properties.Description:
An Endorsement that may be applied to the Insurance Product.

An Endorsement is an amendment to the policy written especially to cover unique items just for you. 

An endorsement is also a change to your policy that is made during the policy's term. An endorsement is attached to your policy to modify the terms of the insurance contract.

Columns.Name: InsuranceEndorsementId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Endorsement.

Columns.Name: InsuranceEndorsementTypeName
Columns.Description: The name of an Insurance Endorsement.

Columns.Name: InsuranceEndorsementTypeDescription
Columns.Description: The description of an Insurance Endorsement.

Columns.Name: InsuranceEndorsementTermsAndConditions
Columns.Description: The terms and conditions associated with the Insurance Endorsement.

Columns.Name: InsuranceEndorsementExclusions
Columns.Description: Exclusions associated with the Insurance Endorsement.

Columns.Name: InsuranceEndorsementTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Insurance Endorsement Type.
